The paper discusses the application of Compressed Sensing (CS) techniques to analog ultrasound signals, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving image quality while reducing data size, which is relevant to Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The use of CS in medical imaging also relates to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as these fields often involve processing large amounts of data.
